412
00:22:39,608 --> 00:22:41,527
About that...

413
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:43,070
Oh, yeah.

414
00:22:43,988 --> 00:22:46,073
Yeah, about that...

415
00:22:46,156 --> 00:22:47,408
I wanna say something...

416
00:22:49,326 --> 00:22:50,911
Oh, about that?

417
00:22:50,995 --> 00:22:53,205
I'm kind of bothered by that.

418
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:57,167
You're mad?

419
00:22:57,251 --> 00:22:58,877
Yeah, I'm pretty upset.

420
00:23:00,129 --> 00:23:03,299
Where did the meat go?

421
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:05,759
I had some of the meat.

422
00:23:05,843 --> 00:23:08,053
We had it for dinner last night.

423
00:23:08,137 --> 00:23:09,138
Why?

424
00:23:10,598 --> 00:23:12,516
I didn't have any.

425
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:13,726
Why?

426
00:23:13,809 --> 00:23:16,812
There wasn't anything else
to make dinner with.

427
00:23:17,855 --> 00:23:19,189
Isn't that a little strange?

428
00:23:22,901 --> 00:23:24,028
I'm sorry.

429
00:23:24,111 --> 00:23:31,118
That meat was from a client who came
all the way from Nagoya to visit Blast.

430
00:23:31,201 --> 00:23:33,203
They run a Yakiniku Restaurant.

431
00:23:33,287 --> 00:23:38,834
They liked their haircuts and our service,
and they went back to Nagoya happy.

432
00:23:38,917 --> 00:23:41,795
And they sent the meat from Nagoya.

433
00:23:41,879 --> 00:23:44,715
They even wrote a letter
saying how to eat it.

434
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:48,969
Explaining exactly how we should cook it.

435
00:23:49,053 --> 00:23:51,305
They specifically wrote a letter about
how to eat it.

436
00:23:52,014 --> 00:23:55,684
I told you that this was from a client.

437
00:23:58,812 --> 00:24:01,023
And that it was from Nagoya.

438
00:24:03,984 --> 00:24:07,780
I have a relationship with my clients.

439
00:24:07,863 --> 00:24:11,075
There's value in the gift.

440
00:24:11,158 --> 00:24:13,619
I'm sorry we ate it without permission.

441
00:24:15,204 --> 00:24:16,789
Of course I'd be upset.

442
00:24:23,087 --> 00:24:28,717
It's hard to draw the line
for things in the fridge.

443
00:24:29,885 --> 00:24:32,012
That's not what I'm talking about.

444
00:24:32,096 --> 00:24:33,931
It was obviously different.

445
00:24:34,973 --> 00:24:38,477
The line doesn't matter here.

446
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:41,230
I'm very sorry.

447
00:24:43,524 --> 00:24:44,525
Whatever.

448
00:25:01,834 --> 00:25:04,795
He's mad we ate it yesterday?

449
00:25:04,878 --> 00:25:06,714
I hadn't told him about it.

450
00:25:11,927 --> 00:25:14,221
I get where he's coming from.

451
00:25:15,139 --> 00:25:17,391
I get it, but...

452
00:25:18,517 --> 00:25:23,147
-We shouldn't have.
-He should've just told us before.

453
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:27,484
But we should've asked him first, too.
Maybe we were wrong.

454
00:25:27,568 --> 00:25:30,612
-We were definitely wrong.
-Usually, you would...

455
00:25:31,363 --> 00:25:33,532
