-Yeah.

509
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:06,393
"That's not
how you're supposed to cook it."

510
00:28:06,476 --> 00:28:07,978
"But it was so fatty..."

511
00:28:08,061 --> 00:28:10,814
-"Did you add oil?"
-"I did."

512
00:28:10,898 --> 00:28:14,776
"It's a teflon pan, so you didn't need to.

513
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:16,904
It's quality meat; it has fat already."

514
00:28:16,987 --> 00:28:18,280
"I'm so sorry."

515
00:28:19,781 --> 00:28:21,199
"That's not enough."

516
00:28:23,118 --> 00:28:24,828
That's totally what he might say.

517
00:28:24,912 --> 00:28:27,414
"Your apology won't bring back the meat."

518
00:28:27,497 --> 00:28:29,791
She should just go buy some meat.

519
00:28:29,875 --> 00:28:32,127
I really hope we end with that scene.

520
00:28:32,210 --> 00:28:34,880
It's been so serious lately.

521
00:28:34,963 --> 00:28:36,506
A light-hearted crime...

522
00:28:36,590 --> 00:28:41,511
If the meat crime is his plan to distract
Natsumi and Minori from their fight,

523
00:28:41,595 --> 00:28:46,266
and if it's a part of Uchi's master plan,
I'd be really impressed.

524
00:28:46,350 --> 00:28:47,351
That's true!

525
00:28:47,434 --> 00:28:51,396
Ah, a common enemy to allowing bonding.

526
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:52,731
How cool is Uchi!

527
00:28:52,814 --> 00:28:54,566
That definitely did not happen!

528
00:28:56,652 --> 00:28:59,446
They might break up over this.

529
00:28:59,529 --> 00:29:02,699
Her boyfriend got mad
because she ate his meat.

530
00:29:03,784 --> 00:29:05,244
You'd be okay with this?

531
00:29:05,327 --> 00:29:08,872
If it were me getting lectured
about meat in front of everyone...

532
00:29:08,956 --> 00:29:13,752
-Well, he's upset on behalf of his client.
-That's right.

533
00:29:13,835 --> 00:29:16,922
But if you're asked why you broke up...

534
00:29:19,383 --> 00:29:22,552
-Break up caused by meat.
-Break up caused by meat.

535
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:26,765
"Yeah, I ate his meat."

536
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:33,188
And if he's asked why they broke up,
he'd say that she ate my meat...

537
00:29:33,272 --> 00:29:34,773
Tori-chan's cracking up.

538
00:29:34,856 --> 00:29:38,026
-You shouldn't laugh.
-It's gonna come back to you.

539
00:29:38,110 --> 00:29:39,861
Tori-chan can't stop.

540
00:29:41,405 --> 00:29:43,824
That was a treat.

541
00:29:43,907 --> 00:29:48,537
Seriously, it's my first time
witnessing a break up caused by meat.

542
00:29:52,708 --> 00:29:53,709
Uchi.

543
00:29:55,168 --> 00:29:56,628
Sorry about before.

544
00:30:00,966 --> 00:30:02,050
It's a mess in here.

545
00:30:02,134 --> 00:30:07,347
I totally thought
it was for everyone to share.

546
00:30:07,431 --> 00:30:10,058
No, it wasn't.

547
00:30:10,142 --> 00:30:11,143
But...

548
00:30:12,185 --> 00:30:14,229
was it something to get so mad about?

549
00:30:14,896 --> 00:30:16,523
You were pretty upset.

550
00:30:16,606 --> 00:30:20,027
I know it's just meat to you guys.

551
00:30:20,110 --> 00:30:23,530
But it was something
that meant a lot to me.

552
00:30:24,364 --> 00:30:29,494
So for you guys, just to go and eat it
like it was nothing

553
00:30:29,578 --> 00:30:31,788
made me really upset.

554
00:30:33,123 --> 00:30:36,877
Like if you got something
from someone special,

555
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:39,004
and if it was treated carelessly...

556
00:30:40,130 --> 00:30:42,632
-Yeah.
-It's the same feeling.

557
00:30:42,716 --> 00:30:46,219
I worked really hard.

558
00:30:46,303 --> 00:30:53,185
And it was my client's recognition
and appreciation of my hard work.

559
00:30:53,268 --> 00:30:56,730
So, for me, it meant a lot.

560
00:30:57,564 --> 00:31:01,651
I understand that you didn't know.

561
00:31:01,735 --> 00:31:04,363
So maybe it couldn't be helped.

562
00:31:04,446 --> 00:31:08,325
But I had told Minori
and she still ate it.

563
00:31:08,408 --> 00:31:12,996
I'm really starting to get angry at her.

564
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:15,415
She didn't tell me
after you guys ate it...

565
00:31:16,333 --> 00:31:18,168
or even before.

566
00:31:19,461 --> 00:31:23,256
And I came home
and found the meat was gone.

567
00:31:23,340 --> 00:31:25,300
Isn't there something wrong there?

568
00:31:25,926 --> 00:31:26,927
Yeah.

569
00:31:27,844 --> 00:31:32,432
I was mad that it was all gone
when I got home.

570
00:31:32,516 --> 00:31:36,311
Either way, I'm sorry.

571
00:31:37,729 --> 00:31:39,773
I need to zone out for a bit.

572
00:31:39,856 --> 00:31:41,650
I don't want to think about anything.

573
00:31:41,733 --> 00:31:43,735
I'll get too upset.

574
00:31:44,528 --> 00:31:46,446
I'm going to the store.
You want anything?

575
00:31:47,322 --> 00:31:50,575
-I'm okay for now.
-A bento or anything?

576
00:31:50,659 --> 00:31:53,328
-You haven't eaten, right?
-I'm okay.

577
00:31:54,287 --> 00:31:57,165
Goodnight then.
I'm sorry.

578
00:32:27,529 --> 00:32:30,532
I'm really sorry.

579
00:32:30,615 --> 00:32:33,034
I know it's all I can say, but I'm sorry.

580
00:32:35,454 --> 00:32:39,791
I can't calm down right now,
no matter what you say.

581
00:32:52,179 --> 00:32:53,472
Goodnight.

